---
// Lesson 12 — a PORTAL is a CROSS-REFERENCE (editorial link between two Anchors,
// already shipped) wrapped by two thin layers that add NOTHING to the data model:
// a GATE (reading progress / collected clues → decides WHEN it shows) and a SKIN
// (glow + transport → decides HOW it feels). Concentric on purpose: the gate and
// the skin sit OVER the cross-reference. The Genesis 1 <-> John 1 "beginning"
// thread is the worked example. WISHLIST (Portal) + CONTEXT ("a Portal is a
// Cross-reference gated by reading progress") + ADR-0005 (design-now-build-later).
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 760 360" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img"
     aria-label="A Portal is a Cross-reference between two Anchors (Genesis 1:1 and John 1:1) wrapped by two layers that add nothing to the data model: a gate that decides when the link shows, and a skin of glow and transport that decides how it feels.">
  <defs>
    <marker id="pg-a" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" refX="7.5" refY="4.5" orient="auto">
      <path d="M0,0 L9,4.5 L0,9 z" fill="#9a7b27"/>
    </marker>
  </defs>

  <text class="ttl" x="40" y="28">PORTAL = a GATE + a SKIN over a CROSS-REFERENCE — no new data model</text>

  <!-- LEFT ANCHOR -->
  <rect class="anc" x="24" y="150" width="156" height="80" rx="8"/>
  <text class="ah" x="102" y="172" text-anchor="middle">Anchor · Genesis 1:1</text>
  <text class="av" x="102" y="196" text-anchor="middle">In the</text>
  <rect class="glow" x="56" y="202" width="92" height="20" rx="6"/>
  <text class="avb" x="102" y="217" text-anchor="middle">beginning</text>

  <!-- RIGHT ANCHOR -->
  <rect class="anc" x="580" y="150" width="156" height="80" rx="8"/>
  <text class="ah" x="658" y="172" text-anchor="middle">Anchor · John 1:1</text>
  <text class="av" x="658" y="196" text-anchor="middle">In the</text>
  <rect class="glow" x="612" y="202" width="92" height="20" rx="6"/>
  <text class="avb" x="658" y="217" text-anchor="middle">beginning</text>

  <!-- CONCENTRIC: SKIN > GATE > CROSS-REFERENCE -->
  <rect class="skin" x="196" y="98" width="368" height="172" rx="16"/>
  <text class="sl" x="212" y="118">SKIN — glow + transport · how it feels (presentation)</text>

  <rect class="gate" x="236" y="134" width="288" height="104" rx="12"/>
  <text class="gl" x="252" y="154">GATE — reading progress / clues · when it shows</text>

  <rect class="core" x="288" y="172" width="184" height="50" rx="8"/>
  <text class="cn" x="380" y="194" text-anchor="middle">CROSS-REFERENCE</text>
  <text class="cd" x="380" y="212" text-anchor="middle">editorial link · two Anchors</text>

  <!-- anchors feed the shipped core -->
  <path class="a" d="M180,196 L286,198" marker-end="url(#pg-a)"/>
  <path class="a" d="M580,196 L474,198" marker-end="url(#pg-a)"/>

  <!-- footer -->
  <text class="foot" x="40" y="300">A Portal adds nothing to the model. The link is already shipped; the gate decides WHEN, the skin decides HOW.</text>
  <text class="foot" x="40" y="320">Read Genesis 1, reach John 1, and "beginning" glows — earned, then it carries you back. A gate and a skin.</text>
</svg>

<style>
  .ttl  { font:700 13px Georgia, serif; fill:#1a1714; letter-spacing:.3px; }
  .anc  { fill:#f3ecdf; stroke:#b9ad93; stroke-width:1.6; }
  .ah   { font:700 11.5px Georgia, serif; fill:#4a443d; }
  .av   { font:12px Georgia, serif; fill:#1a1714; }
  .avb  { font:700 12px Georgia, serif; fill:#1a1714; }
  .glow { fill:#fbf3dc; stroke:#9a7b27; stroke-width:1.3; }
  .skin { fill:#fdf9ee; stroke:#9a7b27; stroke-width:1.6; stroke-dasharray:6 4; }
  .sl   { font:700 11px Georgia, serif; fill:#9a7b27; letter-spacing:.2px; }
  .gate { fill:#fbf3dc; stroke:#9a7b27; stroke-width:1.6; }
  .gl   { font:700 11px Georgia, serif; fill:#4a443d; letter-spacing:.2px; }
  .core { fill:#fff; stroke:#3a5a78; stroke-width:1.8; }
  .cn   { font:700 13px Georgia, serif; fill:#3a5a78; letter-spacing:.3px; }
  .cd   { font:italic 10.5px Georgia, serif; fill:#4a443d; }
  .a    { fill:none; stroke:#9a7b27; stroke-width:2; }
  .foot { font:italic 11px Georgia, serif; fill:#7a6a3a; }
</style>
